dcterms:description: The Michalewicz function is a well-known benchmark function used for optimization problems, characterized by its complex landscape with many local minima. The global minimum is approximately -1.801, located at specific coordinates in a two-dimensional space.
dcterms:title: Michalewicz function

dcterms:creator: Y. Y. Zhang
S. Li
dcterms:description: The Goldstein-Price function is another benchmark function used in optimization, known for its multiple local minima and a global minimum at a specific point. The function is defined over a square domain and is often used to test optimization algorithms.
dcterms:title: Goldstein-Price function
